On 13 Apr 2023, at 14:55, Graham Leggett via dev <dev@httpd.apache.org> wrote:

> Config looks like this:
>
>  <Location /storage>
>    Alias /var/www/dav/storage
>    Dav on
>    AcceptPathInfo On
>  </Location>

Changing the config to this makes it work:

Alias /storage /var/www/dav/storage

It looks like the detail that’s missing that we don’t identify the rest of the URL after the alias and pass it on by calling alias_matches() to identify the prefix:

https://github.com/apache/httpd/blob/trunk/modules/mappers/mod_alias.c#L549

Regards,
Graham
